      "author": "editor@pcgamesn.com",
      "official": false,
      "external": true,
      "image": "https://www.pcgamesn.com/wp-content/sites/pcgamesn/2026/03/slay-the-spire-2-patch-notes-prepared-back-regent-buffs-map-changes-doormaker-rework-900x506.jpg",
      "summary": "Fresh Slay the Spire 2 patch notes have arrived, and Prepared is back. \"You can lower your Shivs,\" developer Mega Crit jokes. Game designer Anthony Giovannetti is here to walk us through the team's thoughts and the design intent behind the new changes. They include some pretty heavy-handed Regent buffs, slightly more friendly map layouts, and yet another fresh approach for one of the roguelike's climactic boss fights. Giovannetti notes that player feedback \"has been instrumental in helping guide our process,\" so keep it coming.\nRead the rest of the story...\nRELATED LINKS:\nTerraria is getting new early game magic, as Re-Logic puts class balance under the microscope\nLost in Random: The Eternal Die proves roguelikes don't need to fill 100 hours\nSlay the Spire 2 is stamping out infinites, and you're not prepared for what we've lost",
      "summaryKo": "최신 패치의 밸런스, 버그 수정, 현지화, 편의성 변경을 보기 쉽게 모았습니다.",
      "body": "Fresh Slay the Spire 2 patch notes have arrived, and Prepared is back. \"You can lower your Shivs,\" developer Mega Crit jokes. Game designer Anthony Giovannetti is here to walk us through the team's thoughts and the design intent behind the new changes. They include some pretty heavy-handed Regent buffs, slightly more friendly map layouts, and yet another fresh approach for one of the roguelike's climactic boss fights. Giovannetti notes that player feedback \"has been instrumental in helping guide our process,\" so keep it coming.\nRead the rest of the story...\nRELATED LINKS:\nTerraria is getting new early game magic, as Re-Logic puts class balance under the microscope\nLost in Random: The Eternal Die proves roguelikes don't need to fill 100 hours\nSlay the Spire 2 is stamping out infinites, and you're not prepared for what we've lost"
